@startuml 02-vault-encryption
title Vault Encryption / Decryption Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam shadowing false

package "Encryption Flow" {
    rectangle "Plaintext Vault\n(JSON)" as plain #E8F5E9

    rectangle "Generate Random IV\n(12 bytes)" as iv #FFF3E0

    rectangle "Build AAD Object" as aad #E3F2FD
    note bottom of aad
        {
          version,
          envelope: {
            vaultId,
            signerDeviceId,
            revision,
            timestamp
          },
          keySlotsDigest
        }
        Canonicalized via JCS (RFC 8785)
    end note

    rectangle "AES-256-GCM\nEncrypt" as encrypt #BBDEFB
    note bottom of encrypt
        - Key: Vault Key (256-bit)
        - IV: 12 random bytes
        - AAD: Binds metadata
        - Tag: 128 bits
    end note

    rectangle "Encrypted Blob\n(ciphertext || tag)" as blob #FFCDD2
}

plain --> iv
iv --> encrypt
aad --> encrypt
encrypt --> blob

package "Decryption Flow" {
    rectangle "Encrypted Blob\n(from storage)" as blob2 #FFCDD2

    rectangle "Extract IV\n(first 12 bytes)" as iv2 #FFF3E0

    rectangle "Rebuild AAD\nfrom Envelope" as aad2 #E3F2FD
    note bottom of aad2
        Must match exactly
        or decryption fails
        (tamper detection)
    end note

    rectangle "AES-256-GCM\nDecrypt" as decrypt #BBDEFB

    rectangle "Plaintext Vault\n(JSON)" as plain2 #E8F5E9

    rectangle "FAIL:\nIntegrity Error" as fail #F44336
}

blob2 --> iv2
iv2 --> decrypt
aad2 --> decrypt
decrypt --> plain2 : Tag Valid
decrypt --> fail : Tag Invalid

note right of blob
    **IV Uniqueness Rule:**
    NEVER reuse IV with
    the same Vault Key
    (catastrophic failure)
end note

note right of fail
    **Tamper Detection:**
    - Modified ciphertext
    - Modified metadata
    - Wrong Vault Key
    All cause auth tag failure
end note

@enduml
